         <div type="chapter" n="1">
            <head rend="cap">perfume</head>
            <div type="section" n="1.1">
               <head rend="cap">sachet powders</head>
               <pb n="100"/>
               
               <!-- GT: Just looking at the structure here, a couple of things:
               1. I think you want another <div> here just enclosing each separate numbered recipe, so from "293" to the next number.
               You can give this <div n="1.1.1">...
               2. the "293" and "frangipanni sachet" look to me like headings for this section #293. I would use <head> for both.
               Or depending on how you want to do it, you could have a single <head> and use @n for 293:
               <head n="293">Frangipanni sachet</head>. Either way... -->
               
               <p n="1.1.1"> 293 </p>
               <p rend="cap">frangipanni sachet.</p>
               <list>
                  <item n="1"><ref target="#GroundSandalwood">Ground Sandalwood</ref>, <measure
                        type="ounce">1 1/2 ounces</measure></item>
                  <item n="1"><ref target="#PowderedOrrisRoot">Powdered Orris Root</ref>, <measure
                        type="ounce">8 ounces</measure></item>
                  <item n="1"><ref target="#GroundTonkBean">Ground Tonka Bean</ref>, <measure
                        type="ounce">1/2 ounce</measure></item>
                  <item n="1"><ref target="#OilofRose">Oil of Rose</ref>, <measure type="drop">5
                        drops</measure></item>
                  <item n="1"><ref target="#OilofNeroli">Oil of Neroli</ref>, <measure type="drop">3
                        drops</measure></item>
               </list>
               <p>Mix them in a mortar very thoroughly.</p>
               <!-- GT: You don't need this linebreak... <p> implies a line-break -->
               <lb/>
               <p n="1.1.2">294</p>
               <p rend="cap">heliotrope sachet</p>
               <list>
                  <item n="1">Powdered Oriss Root, 1/2 pound</item>
                  <item n="1"> Rose Leaves, ground, 4 ounces</item>
                  <item n="1"> Tonka Bean, ground, 2 ounces</item>
                  <item n="1">Vanilla Bean, 1 ounce</item>
                  <item n="1">Grain Musk, 30 grains</item>
                  <item n="1">Oil of Bitter Almond, 1 drop</item>
               </list>
               <p>Mix them</p>
               <lb/>
               <p n="1.1.3">295</p>
               <p rend="cap">millefleurs sachet.</p>
               <list>
                  <item n="1">Powdered Orris Root, 4 ounces</item>
                  <item n="2">Powdered Benzoin, 4 ounces</item>
                  <item n="3">Ground Lavender Flowers, 4 ounces</item>
                  <item n="4">Ground Rose Leaves, 4 ounces</item>
                  <item n="5">Ground Tonka Bean, 1 ounce</item>
                  <item n="6">Ground Vanilla Bean, 1 ounce</item>
                  <pb n="101"/>
                  <item n="7"> Ground Cloves, 1 ounce</item>
                  <item n="8"> Ground Mace, 1/2 ounce</item>
                  <item n="9">Ground Cinnamon, 1 ounce</item>
                  <item n="10">Ground Allspice, 1/2 ounce</item>
                  <item n="11">Ground Sandalwood, 1 ounce</item>
               </list>
               <p>Mix them by sifting. </p>
